miRNA-mRNA regulatory network in TNBC and network diagram of individual target gene


functions.

Critically, the performance advantage of MTI-based modeling was maintained in the

independent GSE19783 validation cohort. While the expression-based model showed substantial

performance degradation when applied to the external dataset, the MTI model retained robust

predictive accuracy. This differential generalization supports our hypothesis that regulatory

relationships encode more stable clinical information than expression levels, which are more

susceptible to technical and biological variation across cohorts.


\begin{figure}[htbp]
